    "Therefore, the theorem follows from (5.20) and r = Then there exists some N 0, M, k 0 ∈ N such that for any K ∈ N with K ≥ N 0, the following is true.",
    "Let i (f i, π i) be a regular formal Lipschitz sum with s( i (f i, π i)) ≤ S. Then there exists an admissible rectangle of order k ≤ k 0 and some n ∈ {0, 1,... K -2} such that the pair of cubesQ = Q(R, n) and Q ′ = Q(R, n + 1) of order k satisfies the estimate | Q i f i det Dπ i - Q ′ i f i det Dπ i | ≤ r d+1 ( √ d + 1)S + r d c d √ Sε.Proof.",
    "The rectangle and the cubes are found in Theorem 5.17.",
    "The estimate then follows from the combination of the estimate in Theorem 5.17 and Lemma 5.6.Finally, we are prepared to construct particularly ill-behaved right hand sides for the PDE (1.3).Suppose we are given some k ∈ N, a bounded function ρ: [0, 1] d → R. We now construct a refinement of ρ at depth k in the following way.",
